smartgov.urban.osm.agent.mover

Class CarMover

  • java.lang.Object
    • smartgov.urban.geo.agent.mover.BasicGeoMover
      • smartgov.urban.osm.agent.mover.CarMover
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GeoMover

    public class CarMover
extends BasicGeoMover
    Used to move an OsmAgentBody in the osm graph, as if it were driving a car.

    Cars move according to a Gipps Model.

      • CarMover

        public CarMover(double maximumAcceleration,
                double maximumBraking,
                double maximumSpeed,
                double vehicleSize)
        CarMover constructor. Parameters are those used in the Gipps' model.
        Parameters:
        maximumAcceleration - maximum car acceleration (m/s-2)
        maximumBraking - negative, maximum car braking (m/s-2)
        maximumSpeed - maximum speed at which the agent should travel (m/s-1)
        vehicleSize - vehicle size, that includes any security margin

        protected void handleArcChanged(GeoArc oldArc,
                                GeoArc newArc)
        Description copied from class: BasicGeoMover
        Defines some behavior that should be applied each time an agent reaches the next arc of the current plan from the mover.

        Example : notify the road containing the new arc that a new agent arrives to handle agents interactions.

        newArc - Current arc

      • updateAgentSpeed

        protected void updateAgentSpeed(GeoAgentBody agentBody)
        Description copied from class: BasicGeoMover
        Called immediately when the moveOn() function is called. By default, will keep the agent speed constant. Can be use to manage acceleration depending on environment perceptions.

      • handleDestinationReached

        protected void handleDestinationReached(GeoAgentBody agentBody,
                                        GeoArc lastArc,
                                        GeoNode lastNode)
        Description copied from class: BasicGeoMover
        Called immediately after the agent as reach it's destination from the moveOn() function, before any other initialization occured.

        Useful for it's reference to the last arc and node crossed.

        Example : To remove an agent from the last road once it has reached the end of it.

        By default, does nothing.

        Overrides:
        handleDestinationReached in class BasicGeoMover
        Parameters:
        agentBody - Agents that reached its destination
        lastArc - last arc crossed
        lastNode - last node crossed
